 a collection of thirteen papers given at the “Third Syntax of the World’s Languages” conference, complemented with four additional papers as well as an introduction by the editors. All contributions deal with clause combining, focusing on one or both of the following two dimensions of analysis: properties of the clauses involved, types of dependency. The studies are data-driven and have a cross-linguistic or typological orientation. In addition to survey papers the volume contains in-depth studies of particular languages, mostly based on original data collected in recent field work.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxClausesvCongresses. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntaxvCongresses. 0aLinguisticsvCongresses. 4aSprachtypologie. 70(DE-588)4158668-20(DE-627)1046579600(DE-576)209844116aSatzverbindung2gnd 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aClause Combining.  aLanguage Typology.1 aArkadiev, Peter M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAuthier, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBickel, Balthasar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aComrie, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCreissels, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCristofaro, Sonia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiessel, Holger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiessel, Holger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFedden, Sebastian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aForker, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators